application /ˌæplɪˈkeɪʃən/

(applications) 

1. N-COUNT An application for something such as a job or membership of an organization is a formal written request for it. 申请 

例： His application for membership of the organization was rejected. 他对该组织会员资格的申请被拒绝了。 

2. N-COUNT In computing, an application is a piece of software designed to carry out a particular task. 应用软件 

例： The service works as a software application that is accessed via the internet. 该业务是一个可以通过因特网访问的软件应用程序。 

3. N-VAR The application of a rule or piece of knowledge is the use of it in a particular situation. 应用 

例： Students learned the practical application of the theory they had learned in the classroom. 学生们学会了课堂上学到的理论的实际应用。 

4. N-UNCOUNT Application is hard work and concentration on what you are doing over a period of time. 勤奋 

例： ...his immense talent, boundless energy and unremitting application. …他的巨大天资、无限精力与不懈努力。

</div>

